  "prompt": "What exactly is Gusto?",
  "response": "Gusto is a cloud-based platform that offers a range of HR, payroll, and benefits services primarily designed for small to medium-sized businesses. Founded in 2011, Gusto aims to simplify the complexities of human resources management by providing tools for payroll processing, tax compliance, employee onboarding, time tracking, and benefits administration.\n\nSome of the key features of Gusto include:\n\n- **Payroll Processing**: Automates payroll calculations, tax withholding, and filing for employees and contractors.\n- **Employee Benefits**: Allows businesses to manage health insurance, retirement plans (like 401(k)s), and other benefits for employees.\n- **Onboarding**: Offers tools to help new hires complete necessary paperwork and integrate into the company.\n- **Time Tracking**: Provides functionality for employees to clock in and out, track hours worked, and manage time-off requests.\n- **HR Tools**: Includes resources for performance management, employee surveys, and compliance with labor laws.\n\nGusto is popular among businesses for its user-friendly interface and the ability to handle multiple HR functions in one place, making it easier for business owners to manage their workforce. Additionally, Gusto offers support and guidance for navigating various HR-related challenges, making it a comprehensive tool for small business owners.",
